title: For Sale/Trade:  SAR-8 Springfield G3 Clone
postcontent: In the late 80s early 90s,  the HK 91 / 93 series were imported by a lot of people, including Springfield. They started importing Greek G3 parts kits and recievers, but then their rifle, the SAR-3, was banned by name. No longer being able to import recievers, Springfield stamped over the "3" and changed it to "8" on the existing recievers, then began making new aluminum cast to accept their remaining parts kits. This one is S/N 14X, and is made on one of the cast recievers. It carries a lifetime warranty from Springfield, very good condition internally, bolt and rollers in very good shape. There are a few scratches here and there externally. $900 or best offer.
